<item>
            <title>[LU-871] clang: minor code cleanups</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-871</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tracking bug for warnings produced by the clang-analyzer static code analysis tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first one is a trivial printk() format warning due to the use of &quot;%Lu&quot; for LPU64, and other places in the code.  The &quot;%L&quot; format specifier is a GCCism that is deprecated in favor of &quot;%ll&quot; from C99.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>FC13 running clang-analyzer-2.8-10.fc13.x86_64</environment>
        <key id="12510">LU-871</key>
            <summary>clang: minor code cleanups</summary>
