                            <comment id="26422" author="knweiss" created="Thu, 12 Jan 2012 07:47:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW I&apos;ve compiled Lustre 2.1.54 patchless client on CentOS 6.2 with Clang&apos;s static analyzer (LLVM 3.0).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I decided to disable the static analyzer check &quot;core.NullDereference&quot; because it detects lots of bugs (521). However, based on a first short glance most of them are dubious because the analyzer seems to get confused by Lustre&apos;s LASSERT(). (And including all of these 521 bugs would make the tarball larger than the Jira upload file limit.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the bug summary:&lt;/p&gt;

